cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving spatial analytics, which involves mining spatial data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, but the most relevant one is likely cs.DB (Databases), as the paper focuses on the differentially private release of data structures that support range queries for counting users' spatial regions. The paper also deals with privacy concerns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses statistical techniques to calibrate privacy-preserving noise, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves computational geometry, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
